  "issue_title": "[Bug] Open PR collateral ignores review_quality_multiplier",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\nOpen-PR collateral is computed from three multipliers (`repo_weight`, `issue`, `label`) but omits `review_quality_multiplier`, diverging from merged-PR earned scoring. An open PR with many maintainer `CHANGES_REQUESTED` reviews is currently charged the same collateral as a clean open PR, overstating its projected merged earned score.\n\nThis is the same class of asymmetry fixed by #613 (label_multiplier) and #691 (state_reason gate) \u2014 open-PR collateral should reflect what the PR would have earned on merge.\n\n## Root cause\n\nThree coupled sites:\n\n**1. `gittensor/classes.py:298-303`** \u2014 `changes_requested_count` is only counted for merged PRs, despite the GraphQL query (`gittensor/utils/github_api_tools.py:122`) fetching `changesRequestedReviews` unconditionally:\n\n```python\nchanges_requested_count = 0\nif is_merged:\n    cr_reviews = pr_data.get('changesRequestedReviews', {}).get('nodes', [])\n    changes_requested_count = sum(\n        1 for r in cr_reviews if r.get('authorAssociation') in MAINTAINER_ASSOCIATIONS\n    )\n```\n\nThis gate was introduced by #305 when the feature only applied to merged PRs. Since then, the data has been fetched but discarded for open PRs.\n\n**2. `gittensor/validator/oss_contributions/scoring.py` \u2014 `calculate_pr_multipliers`** \u2014 hardcodes `pr.review_quality_multiplier = 1.0` for open PRs, so even if the count were populated it would be ignored.\n\n**3. `gittensor/validator/oss_contributions/scoring.py:502-518` \u2014 `calculate_open_pr_collateral_score`** \u2014 the multipliers dict is missing `review_quality`, and the docstring explicitly lists only \"repo_weight, issue, label\" as applicable.\n\n## Impact\n\nAn open PR with N maintainer `CHANGES_REQUESTED` reviews:\n\n- **Current**: collateral charged as if `review_quality_multiplier = 1.0`\n- **Expected**: collateral reduced by `max(0.0, 1.0 - REVIEW_PENALTY_RATE \u00d7 N)`, matching what the merged earned score would be\n\nFor N=3 (\u2192 0.55 multiplier), current collateral is ~1.8\u00d7 the projected merged earned score it was meant to approximate.\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nOpen-PR collateral should apply the same `review_quality_multiplier` that the merged-PR earned score applies, using the same `changes_requested_count` source (`changesRequestedReviews` from GraphQL, restricted to `MAINTAINER_ASSOCIATIONS`).\n\nMultipliers that remain merge-specific (`time_decay`, `credibility`) stay excluded \u2014 those are computed from merge-time state.\n\n## Related precedents\n\n- #612 \u2192 #613 (merged 2026-04-20) \u2014 same shape: added `label_multiplier` to open PR collateral for merged/open consistency\n- #690 \u2192 #691 (merged 2026-04-22) \u2014 same shape: extended `is_valid_issue` state_reason gate to open PR collateral\n\n\n## Environment\n\n- Repository: `entrius/gittensor`\n- Components: `gittensor/classes.py`, `gittensor/validator/oss_contributions/scoring.py`\n- Query path: `gittensor/utils/github_api_tools.py` GraphQL `QUERY` already fetches `changesRequestedReviews` for every PR (no new API cost)\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-04T16:10:37.000Z",
